==Japanese==
=== Interjection ===
'''{{PAGENAME}}''' ([[申し申し]], [[もうしもうし]])

# A [[greeting]] when answering the telephone.  
# An [[interjection]] used when on the phone and attempting to get someone's attention.

==== Etymology ====
* Derives from the verb ''[[mōsu]]'' ([[申す]], [[もうす]]), (humble) "to speak".  ''Mōshi mōshi'' literally means "speaking speaking", and was used in the first telephone experiment in Japan, quite similar to the English "checking, checking" used when testing audio equipment.  In modern parlance, it is used more like English "hello", only just on the telephone, or figuratively when trying to get through to someone.  

==== Notes ====
This term has been used in [[Europe]] and in the [[United States]] as a name for things such as stores, restaurants, record labels and bands. A [[Google]] search of the term results in 1,220,000 non-Japanese counts of the word &mdash; written in [[romaji|Latin characters]] [http://www.google.com/search?client=safari&rls=en&q=moshi+moshi&ie=UTF-8&oe=UTF-8].

